This is version 3.2 of this map. I added some light and fixed a few textures. This time the download comes with two maps. The two maps have the same layout, but have different weapon options.


--- fy_iceworld_2006_v32
  All players spawn with the same random weapon. (no buy zone) This is what makes this map one of a kind!


--- fy_iceworld_2006_v32_buyzone
  Weapons are on the gound with a buy zone in the middle. Similar to the original fy_iceworld. (all weapons come with full ammo)




=====EDIT======
The map that has no buyzone might crash your server after running it for about a hour. Now that GunGames mod is out this map is kinda useless. Look for fy_iceworld_midnight if your looking for a good iceworld map.

FY_ICEWORLD_09_V2 BY )v(eatshield

As with other fy_iceworld maps, weapons are on the 
ground near spawn and there is a buy zone in the middle. 
This map is different to that there are several places to 
hide and that there is water in the middle. 

A few changes have been made in this map from FY_ICEWORLD_09.
The corners are now rounder, the bridge has been changed to 
look like wooden planks. The water now only damages your armor not your health.

Fy_iceworld_09 By )v(eatShield

Just a remake for iceworld. This map has many/several places to hide. The pictures help to explain the areas. The 4 corners have places to hide inside. Behind ct and t spawn is a a place. Both sides of the buy zone against the far wall. 

This map took only a few days to make and I think it turned out good.

I never found a fy_iceworld2k for CS:S that resembled 'the most' to the original, so I started to work on what could be considered a 'direct port'. Development actually began back in 2016, but I took a two-year hiatus while working on maps for the classic Counter-Strike game. Now I decided to get back and finish this map, renaming it into "fy_iceworld2k18".

I was aiming for a larger style fy_iceworld type map.

The map supports 64 players with enough weapons for everyone.

the map is roughly 4 times the size of fy_iceworld, has many nooks and crannies in the cliffs to camp. there are snowdrifts and unique barricades to add the cover.

I would recommend 22 - 64 players on this map.

This map took me about 3 - 5 days to complete.

The ceiling is also raised so those low gravity servers can enjoy the map too.

the bug (and see the results).

cheers,

A rendition of the iceworld FY map, except a little bigger! guns and spawn points are almost the same both teams also have buy zones.

This is more of a test to try new texture effects and see what limits could be pushed and not!

What came out of this test:

The level has great FPS considering it's wall-to-wall displacements, even for my crappy machine!
got to create and work with selflit textures
got to create and work with texture blending
got to see what options for translucency and alfa transparency can be used with blending

the complete texture pack can be found as IcePac 1 on fpsbanana.com here
http://www.fpsbanana.com/textures/765
it's not needed to run the map since they are packed in the bsp file, this is here for those who would like to use the textures in there own maps!


if this would be better with out buy zones or if there are any other suggestions let me know!
